  "response": "Here are some less-famous but interesting sights in Aurora, IL:\n\n1. Philips Park\n- Includes a small zoo\n- Has walking trails and scenic areas\n- Features historic log cabin and museum\n\n2. SciTech Interactive Science Museum\n- Hands-on science exhibits\n- Great for families and children\n- Interactive learning experiences\n\n3. Paramount Theatre\n- Historic theater with beautiful architecture\n- Hosts various performances and events\n- Located in downtown Aurora\n\n4. Fox River Trail\n- Nice walking and biking path\n- Scenic views along the river\n- Good for outdoor recreation\n\n5. Aurora Historical Society\n- Offers insights into local history\n- Preserves historical artifacts\n- Located in the David L. Pierce Arts and History Center\n\n6. Nicholas Conservatory and Gardens\n- Botanical gardens\n- Greenhouse with diverse plant collections\n- Located near Rock Cut State Park\n\n7. Walsh Park\n- Offers recreational facilities\n- Has sports fields and walking paths\n- Good for outdoor activities\n\nThese attractions are less touristy but can provide interesting experiences for visitors to Aurora.",
